    {
      "para_id": "Q001851.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(o 1) For Nanna , the fierce calf of An , lord , the firstborn child of Enlil , his master , Ibbi-Suen , the god of his land , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters , fashioned an image of the Meluhhan leopard brought to him as a diplomatic gift from Marḫaši . He dedicated it to him for his well-being . The name of this leopard is „May it be caught !\""
    }
  ],
